goal.parser

Class ParsedObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • goal.parser.ParsedObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IParsedObject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ParsedObject>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Action, ActionCombo, ActionSpecification, AgentFile, EnvironmentInfo, GOALProgram, ImportCommand, Launch, Macro, MASProgram, MentalLiteral, MentalStateCondition, Message, Module, Rule, RuleSet, Selector, TrueLiteral, UserSpecAction.PrePost

    public class ParsedObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ParsedObject>, IParsedObject

    Object that originates from a parser. E.g., the result of parsing a file.

    Saves a marker where the object was defined in the parser's stream. This enables a Validator to indicate where a parsing issue was found.

    Author:
    N.Kraayenbrink

        public void setID(int id)

      • getID

        public int getID()

      • getSource

        public InputStreamPosition getSource()
        Returns the source code location in the input stream of the object that was parsed.
        Specified by:
        getSource in interface IParsedObject
        Returns:
        The InputStreamPosition, i.e., location of this object's definition in the stream where it was found. May return null which usually indicates that the object has been inserted manually, and not by a parser.
